UNITED STATES SAVINGS & LOAN CO. v. PARKER et al. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. May 25, 1903.) No. 916. Appeal from the Circuit Court of the United States for the District of Oregon. J. Thorburn Ross, E. B. Seabrook, Wm. A. Munly, and John K. Kollock, for appellant. J. Q. A. Bowlby, for appellee H. B. Parker.

Before GILBERT, ROSS, and MORROW, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On the authority of The Pacific States Savings, Loan and Building Company, a corporation, v. Lizzie A. Green et al. (just decided) 123 Fed. 43, the judgment is reversed, and cause remanded to the court below, with directions to overrule the demurrer to the bill, with leave to the defendants to answer.
